:: CarSharingDoubleUpOffer
<<set $step = 0>><<ShowInfo>><<set $day += 45>>

<h3>A New Proposal</h3>
<div class="consequence-text">
	<p>Six weeks of sharing the car. It's been working remarkably well. You coordinate schedules, split gas costs, and help each other out when emergencies arise. The trust you've built is real.</p>
	<p>One evening, the other family invites you over for dinner. After the meal, as your wives chat and the children play, the husband brings up something they've been discussing.</p>
	<p>"The car-sharing has been great," he says. "We've been thinking... both our families are paying around $<<= $housingCost>> in rent each month. That's a lot of money."</p>
	<p>He pauses, then continues: "What if we doubled up? Shared an apartment the way we share the car? We could each pay much less instead. Save hundreds every month."</p>
	<p>Your wife is immediately hesitant. "We'd be living together? In one apartment?"</p>
	<p>"It wouldn't be forever," the other wife says. "Just until we both save enough to get ahead. Maybe a year. We've proven we can work together with the car."</p>
	<p>You do the math in your head: cutting rent in half could mean thousands of dollars saved in a year. That's significant money for emergencies, sending money back home, or saving for a better future.</p>
	<p>But your wife is pregnant. She'll give birth in the next few weeks. Privacy during that time matters.</p>
</div>
<hr>

<h4>What do you decide?</h4>
<div class="housing-choice">
	<<link "Accept the housing double-up offer">><<goto "AffordableDoubleUpHousing">><</link>>
	<p><em>Share an apartment with the car-sharing family. Your rent drops significantly each month, saving real money. But you'll have less privacy, and your wife will be giving birth soon. The car-sharing has worked well - maybe this will too.</em></p>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="housing-choice">
	<<link "Decline - keep separate housing">><<goto "DeclineDoubleUp">><</link>>
	<p><em>Thank them for the offer but maintain separate housing. You'll keep paying your current rent, but you'll have privacy for your growing family. The car-sharing arrangement can continue without the added complexity of living together.</em></p>
</div>

:: AffordableDoubleUpHousing
<<set $step = 0>><<ShowInfo>>
<<set _originalHousingCost = $housingCost>>
