<<set $doubleUpLiving = true>>
<<set $familyHealth -= 12>><<set $day += 14>>

<h3>Doubled-Up Living</h3>
<div class="consequence-text">
	<p>You decide to accept. You move into the slightly larger of the two apartments - a two-bedroom that can fit both families if you're creative with space.</p>
	<p>Your share of the rent is now $<<= $housingCost>> per month, down from $<<= _originalHousingCost>>. The savings are real and immediate.</p>
	<p>But so are the challenges. Two families, one apartment. You share the kitchen, the bathroom, the living space. Your wives coordinate cooking schedules. The children share toys and create noise. Every decision requires communication and compromise.</p>
	<p>Your wife is in her final weeks of pregnancy. She's anxious about giving birth with another family living just feet away. "Where will I recover?" she asks quietly one night. "How will we have any privacy?"</p>
	<p>You share a car. Now you share a home. The trust is strong, but you're about to test it in ways you didn't anticipate.</p>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="stats-box">
	<p style="margin:4px 0;font-size:0.9em;">
