</div>
<hr>
<<link "Continue" "AffordableCSectionCrisis">><</link>>

:: DeclineDoubleUp
<<set $step = 0>><<ShowInfo>>

<h3>Maintaining Boundaries</h3>
<div class="consequence-text">
	<p>You thank them for the offer, but explain that with the baby coming, you need to keep your own space. Your wife needs privacy for the birth and recovery.</p>
	<p>"We understand," the other husband says. "The car-sharing is working great - let's keep that going. Maybe we can revisit the housing idea later, after your baby is born and things settle down."</p>
	<p>Your wife is visibly relieved when you get home. "I was so worried you'd say yes," she admits. "Sharing the car is one thing. Sharing our home while I'm giving birth? That felt like too much."</p>
	<p>You'll continue paying your current rent, but you'll have the privacy and space your family needs during this critical time. The car-sharing partnership continues strong, and your relationship with the other family remains positive.</p>
	<p>Sometimes maintaining boundaries is the wisest choice.</p>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="success-box">
	<p style="color: green;"><strong>Outcome:</strong> You've preserved both your privacy and your relationship with the car-sharing family by setting clear boundaries. The partnership continues without the added stress of shared living.</p>
</div>
