:: AffordableRespectPrivacy
<<set $step = 0>><<ShowInfo>><<set $day += 14>>

<h3>Respect and Cooperation</h3>
<div class="consequence-text">
	<p>You don't bring in your wife's friend out of respect for the other family. It's tough for the first two weeks. You're exhausted, trying to work while helping your wife recover, caring for the newborn, and managing the crowded household.</p>
	<p>But something unexpected happens.</p>
	<p>The wife of the other family sees how hard you're struggling. She's been through this herself. One morning, she knocks on your door.</p>
	<p>"I can help," she says. "I know what it's like. Let me watch the baby for a few hours so you both can rest."</p>
	<p>From that point on, both families begin working together. They help with the baby. You help with their kids. Cooking becomes shared. The apartment is still cramped, but it feels less like a desperate arrangement and more like a community.</p>
	<p>Your wife recovers well. The baby is healthy. The other family appreciates that you respected their boundaries, and the trust between you has deepened.</p>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="success-box">
	<p style="color: green;"><strong>Success:</strong> By respecting the other family's boundaries, you've strengthened the partnership. The housing and car-sharing arrangements continue successfully.</p>
</div>

