<<set $step = 0>><<ShowInfo>><<set $day += 14>>

<h3>Financial Arrangement</h3>
<div class="consequence-text">
	<p>You approach the other family with a proposal: you'll pay a larger share of the rent if the other wife can help your wife during her recovery. After discussion, they agree. You'll now pay a significantly larger share while they pay less.</p>
	<p>At first, it works. The other wife helps with the baby, prepares meals, and checks on your wife throughout the day.</p>
	<p>But problems emerge quickly.</p>
	<p>The two wives have fundamentally different approaches to childcare. Your wife believes in letting the baby cry briefly to develop independence. The other wife thinks babies should never be left to cry. Tensions build over parenting philosophies.</p>
	<p>Then there's the question of responsibility. Did the agreement include doing your wife's laundry? Cleaning your side of the apartment? Where does "helping with recovery" end and "being a servant" begin?</p>
	<p>Arguments start. Quiet at first, then loud enough that both families can hear through the thin walls. The atmosphere becomes toxic.</p>
	<p>The conflict escalates until it affects everything you share, including the car. After a particularly heated argument, the other family announces they want to end both arrangements.</p>
	<p>"We can't do this anymore," they say. "We're moving out, and we're taking the car. We need it more, and frankly, we can't stand being around you anymore."</p>
	<p>You're too exhausted from the conflict to fight about it.</p>
</div>
